<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-12-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-12-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="121" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d121">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/438–439.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Chargé <persName type="to">de
                                    Billier</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-12-08"><hi rend="italic">December 8,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 34.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The department acknowledges the receipt of
                            your unnumbered dispatch of the 11th ultimo, with which was inclosed a
                            copy of the Persian Government’s acceptance of the invitation of this
                            Government to send delegates to the joint commission on the opium
                            question at Shanghai.</p>
                        <p>You are instructed to express anew to the foreign office the
                            gratification of this Government that Persia will participate in a
                            conference which, it is hoped, will be instrumental in contributing
                            toward the suppression of the opium evil.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>